cs.MS, cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.CE

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on comparing the performance of different software packages for sparse matrix-vector multiplication. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper deals with numerical computations and performance evaluation. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of different architectures (multi-core CPUs and GPUs). 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is a possibility as the paper discusses the performance of different software packages on modern architectures. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the paper deals with large matrices commonly encountered in scientific and engineering applications.
